🌿💧 Nirjala Ekadashi — the most sacred and spiritually intense of all Ekadashis. Observed with absolute fasting — not even a drop of water, it’s a day of deep devotion to Lord Vishnu. 🕉️✨

🙏 It is said that observing this fast bestows the fruits of all 24 Ekadashis combined, bringing purity, blessings, and liberation (moksha).

🌾 On this holy day, many also perform daan of jal bhare matke (donating clay pots filled with water) — a symbol of relief and compassion — and arrange Brahman Bhoj, feeding learned Brahmins as a sacred act of charity and reverence.

🪔 May Lord Vishnu bless us all with strength, devotion, and inner peace.

Kailash Dham Temple in Bishangarh, Jalore District, Rajasthan features a 72-feet tall Shiva statue and a cave with replicas of all 12 Jyotirlingas. It allows devotees to experience the spiritual essence of all Jyotirlingas in one place.

12 Jyotirlingas of India — Divine Abodes of Lord Shiva

From the sacred shores of Somnath to the snow-capped peaks of Kedarnath, each Jyotirlinga carries its own legend and spiritual energy. Visit the places where Shiva is believed to still reside — ancient, powerful, and eternal.
